        {
          "provision_label_raw": "section",
          "text": "The intent of this chapter is to regulate the use and preservation of privately owned open spaces, including golf courses, driving ranges, and similar recreational lands, recognizing their dual role as community amenities and significant landscaped areas within the urban fabric. These lands are intended primarily for outdoor recreational use, while maintaining their contribution to the City's green space network, stormwater management, and ecological systems.",
